          "id": "medmcqa-0be9175d-db8c-4da5-840c-38cb1060028d",
          "text": "A 30-year-old patient complains of pain abdomen for 5 days, with similar history in recent past as well. On examination, localized tenderness in right upper quadrant on deep palpation is observed. A slight yellowish discoloration of skin is noted as well. USG examination reveals the following findings. If this patient had associated gallstones, which of the following would it be?",
