          "explanation": "Stiripentol\nStiripentol increases GABA transmission. It is granted orphan drug status for the treatment of Dravet’s syndrome (Severe myoclonic epilepsy in infants).\nIcatibant is a bradykinin B2 receptor antagonist. It is used for acute attacks of hereditary angioedema in adults with C1-esterase inhibitor deficiency.\nPitolisant (a/k/a Tiprolisant) is a inverse agonist of H3 receptor. It is under trial for schizophrenia and Parkinson’s disease.\nTafamidis stabilizes the correctly folded tetrameric form of TTR. It is used in familial amyloid polyneuropathy."
