          "explanation": "The Fick equation is a useful method for measuring cardiac output or flow through any organ when the oxygen (O2) consumption and the difference between arterial and venous O2 content (vol% = ml/100ml) is known.\nFlow = O2 consumption /  arterial (O2 content – venous O2 content)\nCardiac output = O2 consumption / (aorta O2 – pulmonary artery O2)\n= 400 / (20 – 15)\n= 8 L/min"
