          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans is 'a' i.e. Leukemia o Leukemia is the most common radiation-induced cancer. All leukemias, except CLL, can be caused by radiationso Other tumors caused by radiation exposure are thyroid carcinoma (especially papillary carcinoma), breast cancer and skin cancers (squamous cell and melanoma)."
