          "explanation": "Chest X-rays reveal a patchy, diffuse bronchopneumonia involving both lobes. CT scan reveals Ground glass opacity of interstitial change along with air bronchogram The classical friend egg appearance of the colonies of Mycoplasma pneumoniae. The description suggests atypical pneumonia caused by Mycoplasma pneumoniae. Patients often remain ambulatory throughout the illness, hence the name \"walking pneumonia.\" The disease remits after 3 to 10 days without specific treatment X-ray abnormalities resolve more slowly in 2 weeks to 2 months. In legionellosis - WBCs are elevated In viral infections- WBCs are below normal",
