          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "This is a case of acute pericarditis. ECG in acute pericarditis typically shows diffuse ST elevation. Presents with chest pain as the main symptom. Most common fungal cause of acute pericarditis is Histoplasma. OPTION A shows the yeast cells with the pseudohyphae classical of Candida. Option B shows septate hyphae with dichotomous branching- seen in Aspergillus Option C shows budding yeast cells - seen in Histoplasma Option D shows India ink staining - seen in Cryptococcus.",
