          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "This patient most likely has Alzheimer's disease. In advanced disease atrophy is most pronounced in temporoparietal lobes and hippocampus. Several genes play an impoant role in the pathogenesis of AD. One is the APP gene on chromosome 21. Presenilin-1 (PSEN-1) is on chromosome 14. Presenilin-2 The Apo e4 allele confers increased risk of AD in the general population.",
