          "explanation": "The bleeding is likely from wounded liver. The surgeon attempts to occlude the free edge of lesser omentum also known as hepatoduodenal ligament. This maneuver is also known as Pringle's maneuver. Occlusion of hepatoduodenal ligament occludes the following structures: Hepatic aery Poal vein Common bile duct However, if the bleeding does not stop even after occlusion of these structures, the likely source of bleeding is inferior vena cava or hepatic veins.",
