          "explanation": "This is a case of acute chest syndrome in a patient of sickle cell anemia. Presents as acute fever, cough, chest pain and wheezing in a background of sickle cell anemia. X-ray and CT are suggestive of subsegmental atelectasis of right lower lobe. Management: - Transfusion to maintain hematocrit > 30% Emergency exchange transfusion Hydroxyurea is the mainstay.",
