          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ref. The Short Textbook of Pediatrics. Pg 644\n \n\nDactylitis (also called hand-foot syndrome) is painful swelling of the hands or feet.\nThis is often the first symptom that may show up in small infants or toddlers with sickle cell disease. \nDactylitis is caused by sickled red blood cells blocking the small blood vessels in the hands and feet.\n\n \nOther causes\n\nTB\nSarcoidosis\nSyphilis\nSpondyloarthritis\nInfection - Commonly caused by skin infections, such as Streptococcus or Staphylococcus"
