          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans-DNote-Weber's syndrome (superior alternating hemiplegia) is a form of stroke characterized by the presence of an ipsilateral oculomotor nerve palsy and contralateral hemiparesis or hemiplegia."
