          "explanation": "The recurrence of abnormal vaginal bleeding in a patient with a previous history of a cone biopsy would raise concerns of carcinoma of the cervix.\nHer last smear was nearly five years ago,indicating she defaulted from follow-up after her cone biopsy.\nSix weeks amenorrhoeamight raise concerns about an ectopic pregnancy but the absence of pain makes this unlikely.\nIt would always be wise to perform a pregnancy test and scan if in any about."
