          "text": "A 20-year-old male presented to the OPD with high-grade fever, groin pain and a swollen scrotum for 1 week and are worsening progressively. On examination, Tender inguinal lymphadenopathy Scrotal swelling with hydrocoele Lymphatic streaking Blood samples are taken and a parasite infection is suspected. The above disease is transmitted by which of the following vectors: -",
