          "explanation": "This is a case of filariasis (acute lymphadenitis) due to Wuchereria bancrofti. Microfilariae are found in blood, hydrocoele and other body fluids. Most commonly spread by the Culex mosquito. Signs and symptoms Fever Inguinal or axillary lymphadenopathy Testicular and/or inguinal pain Skin exfoliation Limb or genital swelling - Repeated episodes of inflammation and lymphedema lead to lymphatic damage, chronic swelling, and elephantiasis of the legs, arms, scrotum, vulva, and breasts Image A - Anopheles mosquito Image B - Culex mosquito Image C - Aedes mosquito Image D - Rat flea",
