          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ref. Robbins Pathology. 9th edition. Page. 517\n \nHemangioma\nThese tumours are slow growing and are generally asymptomatic unless they exert mass effect on sensitive structures.\n \nMicroscopy\n\nClosely packed spindle cells with spaces containing little blood\nLumens may be thrombosed or organized, hemosiderin present due to rupture\nScant fibrous stroma"
