          "text": "A 28 year old male presented with rash on his arms, legs and face, and painful ulceration of his lips and mouth along with fever. He developed an acute sore throat and conjunctivitis, following which a diagnosis of acute pharyngitis was made, presumed streptococcal, and oral penicillin was prescribed. All of the following can be used in the treatment of the above disease except: -",
