          "explanation": "Ans: c (Asphyxia, syncope, coma) Ref: Reddy, 27th ed, p. 121The different modes of death are:AsphyxiaSyncopeComaSomatic death:Complete irreversible stoppage of circulation, breathing, and brain functionBrain death:Features of brain death are deep coma, no breathing, no cardiac function, no reflexes, fixed dialated pupil and flat EEGMolecular death:Death of cells or tissue individually"
