          "explanation": "This is a case of hairy cell leukemia. Bone marrow biopsy image shows the classical fried egg appearance. Flow cytometry study revealed that the cells were positive for CD11c, CD103, CD123 and CD25 and were also TRAP positive Treatment: - Splenectomy is often associated with prolonged remission. Nucleosides including cladribine and deoxycoformycin are highly active Interferon a is also an effective therapy but is not as effective as nucleosides. Chemotherapy-refractory patients have responded to vemurafenib, a BRAF inhibitor.",
