          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Retinoblastoma\nIncidence:  It is the most common intraocular tumor of childhood occurring 1 in 20,000 live births.\nAge : though congenital, it is not recognized at birth, and is usually seen between 1 and 2 years of age.\nSex : There is no sex predisposition.\nRace : it is rarer in Negroes than whites.\nBilaterality : In 25-30% cases, there is bilateral involvement, although one eye is affected more extensively and earlier than the other."
