          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Pseudoephedrine, a mixed direct- and indirect-acting sympathomimetic, may raise blood pressure and car­diac oxygen requirement, potentiate the cardiac effects of thyroid hormone, and increase urinary retention in patients with prostatic hypertrophy. It is not contrain­dicated in cases of urinary incontinence, and may actually be useful in select patients with the condition because it contracts the bladder sphincter."
