          "explanation": "Ref. Textbook of Biochemistry for Medical Students. Page. 230\n \nStraight forward easy question.\nChaperones\n\nProtein folding is an essential step in the fi al synthesis of any protein. ere is a class of specialized proteins, chaperones, whose function is to assist in this process.\nMolecular chaperones function in many cell compartments, including the endoplasmic reticulum, where extensive protein synthesis occurs.\nFailure to fold correctly usually results in eventual destruction of the protein."
