          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "The patient has sinusoidal ventricular rhythm, which is due to electrolyte abnormality in above case. The patient has USG repo suggestive of CKD due to raised coical echogenicity. AV fistula in forearm is suggestive that patient undergoes dialysis but may have missed and landed up in hyperkalemia. As a pa of management, defibrillation and control of hyperkalemia is priority while emergency hemodialysis is being readied.",
