          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "C. (818 - S. Das) Barium oesophagogram in carcinoma esophagus shows 1. Irregular mucosal filling defect 2. Distortion of the esophageal lumen 3. Annular stricture 4. Irregular \"rat - tail\" filling defect of the distal esophagus with a shouldered edge 5. Edges of filling defect are usually sharp and clear-cut ** Tertiary waves consist of non-propulsive disorganized contractions which fail to advance the barium bolus (AI 09) * \"Apple core sign \" is a feature of carcinoma of colon** * Bird of prey\" sign is seen in the radiographic barium examination of - Sigmoid volvulus**"
