          "text": "A patient comes to the OPD complaining of the worst headache of his life and sudden onset of massive epistaxis from left nostril. The bleeding stopped as abruptly as it staed for which she underwent nasal packing. There was no history of diabetes, hypeension, local trauma or surgery. Patient also complained of visual loss along with unbearable retro-orbital pain. CECT head along with DSA was ordered immediately. Which extraocular muscle is likely to get affected in the above condition?",
