          "id": "medmcqa-60fbe84c-b02f-47d8-a807-34068ecfe3f0",
          "text": "A 70-year-old man presents with the deterioration of vision 3 weeks after cataract extraction and lOL implantation. Slit lamp examination shows honeycomb maculopathy and Florescinangiography (Fshows 'flower petal'hyperfluorescence. The most likely diagnosis is -",
