          "explanation": "Image shows a cyanosed child. An infant or a newborn with CHD that is dependent on the patency of the ductus aeriosus for survival can be termed as having a duct-dependent lesion. Neonates with duct-dependent physiology require prostaglandin El (PGEl) for survival. Early recognition of a duct-dependent situation allows early initiation of PGEl and stabilization until definitive procedure is accomplished",
