          "text": "A 50-year-male patient presented to the ER with scrotal swelling which extended to the anterior abdominal wall and upper thigh. The patient gave a history of falling on the cross beam of a bicycle last evening. With history, clinical examination & relevant investigations doctor on duty reached to diagnosis of urethral tear. What is the epithelium seen at the most probable location of tear in urethra in this patient?",
